    {"id":"post_1","type":"sharp_opinion","source_theme":"flaw_first_pitch","text":"Voluntarily naming what your company does not do well is still one of the fastest ways to stop sounding like a property manager in pitch mode.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"sharpest_observation","best_timing":"early_week","publish_after_linkedin":false,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"transparent_sales_leader","source_file":"linkedin/post_1.txt","theme":"flaw_first_pitch","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_2","type":"recognition","source_theme":"buyer_verified_pipeline","text":"'Contract sent' is not pipeline progress. It's stationery.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"recognition_line","best_timing":"mid_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"transparent_sales_leader","source_file":"linkedin/post_2.txt","theme":"buyer_verified_pipeline","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_2.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_3","type":"recognition","source_theme":"overpromising_future_churn","text":"Over-promising revenue is just delayed churn with better onboarding photos.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"recognition_line","best_timing":"mid_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"transparent_sales_leader","source_file":"linkedin/post_3.txt","theme":"overpromising_future_churn","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_3.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_4","type":"diagnostic","source_theme":"buyer_action_stages","text":"A deal is only moving if the owner is moving. Shared numbers, introduced spouse, asked about timing, named a go-live date. Everything else is mostly seller cardio.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"tactical_question","best_timing":"after_post_1","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"transparent_sales_leader","source_file":"linkedin/post_2.txt","theme":"buyer_action_stages","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_2.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_5","type":"story_detail","source_theme":"three_scenario_forecast","text":"Same actual result, two different emotional outcomes: promise $100k and deliver $90k, you're a disappointment. Promise $80k and deliver $90k, you're the hero. Expectations do a lot of P&L work.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"story_detail","best_timing":"mid_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"transparent_sales_leader","source_file":"linkedin/post_3.txt","theme":"three_scenario_forecast","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_3.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_6","type":"engagement","source_theme":"constraint_transparency","text":"Which truth is hardest for VRMs to say early enough: 'we're not the cheapest,' 'we're not a fit for every owner,' or 'that revenue number isn't realistic for your property'?","engagement_prompt":true,"post_role":"conversation_opener","best_timing":"late_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"transparent_sales_leader","source_file":"newsletter/newsletter.txt","theme":"constraint_transparency","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_7","type":"channel_connector","source_theme":"vrm_sales_library_bridge","text":"Went deeper on this in the VRM Sales Library because transparent selling in VRM is not about being nice. It's about reducing the gap between what gets sold and what the owner later experiences.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"cross_channel_bridge","best_timing":"end_of_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"transparent_sales_leader","source_file":"newsletter/newsletter.txt","theme":"vrm_sales_library_bridge","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_3.txt"}}
